He's been a friend of mine.

00:00:41.280 --> 00:00:43.870
He was a former student,
briefly, at NEC,

00:00:43.870 --> 00:00:47.340
and gone on to great,
wonderful things,

00:00:47.340 --> 00:00:49.390
including travels
around the world,

00:00:49.390 --> 00:00:51.220
as you can see by
the bio so we're

00:00:51.220 --> 00:00:53.890
very fortunate that
he's here today.

00:00:53.890 --> 00:00:56.250
He's got an assignment
on the handout which

00:00:56.250 --> 00:00:58.250
he'll talk about
as we go through.

00:00:58.250 --> 00:01:00.380
And that'll be due
next Monday like we've

00:01:00.380 --> 00:01:02.720
done before with other
of our presenters.

00:01:02.720 --> 00:01:05.200
Don't forget, Wednesday we
have a concert with Neil

00:01:05.200 --> 00:01:07.180
and an associate
Robin Eubanks, who's

00:01:07.180 --> 00:01:10.000
one of the great
improvisers on the scene

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:12.200
today, wonderful trombonist.

00:01:12.200 --> 00:01:14.830
So they'll be in Killian Hall,
