the sounds, what it was

01:14:40.272 --> 01:14:42.730
like after you recorded them
because everything's different

01:14:42.730 --> 01:14:44.680
after you record it.

01:14:44.680 --> 01:14:46.940
The classic example
are gunshots.

01:14:46.940 --> 01:14:48.956
You think a gunshot
would be powerful.

01:14:48.956 --> 01:14:50.580
But when they made
the film Terminator,

01:14:50.580 --> 01:14:54.420
they took Howitzer's, and
cannons, and bazookas,

01:14:54.420 --> 01:14:57.320
and they put them all together
to make these guns that Arnold

01:14:57.320 --> 01:15:00.660
Schwarzenegger would shoot to
make them sound like comic book

01:15:00.660 --> 01:15:02.240
big, larger than life.

01:15:02.240 --> 01:15:04.800
But guns don't sound
larger than life.

01:15:04.800 --> 01:15:07.260
They sound smaller than
life, just like a little pop.

01:15:10.110 --> 01:15:13.420
In Hollywood, there
is a job in Hollywood,

01:15:13.420 --> 01:15:17.630
should you be interested,
in making guns sound big.

01:15:17.630 --> 01:15:19.850
Many of my students
go and do that stuff.

01:15:24.770 --> 01:15:26.640
So why did you want
to record these?

01:15:26.640 --> 01:15:29.098
What was your initial thought
about recording these sounds?

01:15:29.098 --> 01:15:32.170
Like, the kitchen, my
