01:16:28.325 --> 01:16:31.900
Once you had those
sounds, how did you

01:16:31.900 --> 01:16:33.510
go from there to
finishing a piece?

01:16:33.510 --> 01:16:36.110
So as you see with me,
it's like, I come up

01:16:36.110 --> 01:16:37.080
with some cool sounds.

01:16:37.080 --> 01:16:38.820
I record some
elevators, some bells.

01:16:38.820 --> 01:16:41.270
And sometimes I just start
messing with the stuff.

01:16:41.270 --> 01:16:44.245
But at some point, it's
actually got to finish a piece.

01:16:44.245 --> 01:16:47.230
So once I start to set
out to make a piece,

01:16:47.230 --> 01:16:51.004
then typically I'm beginning
to think of what kind of shape

01:16:51.004 --> 01:16:51.920
should the piece have?

01:16:51.920 --> 01:16:53.500
I have a degree in
music composition

01:16:53.500 --> 01:16:57.170
so I kind of neurotically
have to deal with it that way.

01:16:57.170 --> 01:16:57.920
You don't have to.

01:16:57.920 --> 01:17:02.940
And I think any way you
deal with it can potentially

01:17:02.940 --> 01:17:04.640
be successful.

01:17:04.640 --> 01:17:10.590
But one of the things I learned
from a teacher I had was

01:17:10.590 --> 01:17:13.940
that the first thing you do
when you write a piece of music

01:17:13.940 --> 01:17:16.810
is you decide the duration.

01:17:16.810 --> 01:17:20.610
The second you can do is can
could think about the form.

01:17:20.610 --> 01:17:23.560
And when you're thinking about
the form, the order in which

01:17:23.560 --> 01:17:27.410
stuff's going to happen,
you're actually preparing,

01:17:27.410 --> 01:17:29.350
if you call this
composition, you're

01:17:29.350 --> 01:17:32.180
actually composing music
without hearing a sound.

01:17:32.180 --> 01:17:35.860
I could think start
soft, end loud.

01:17:35.860 --> 01:17:38.830
I could think, start
fast, end slow.

01:17:38.830 --> 01:17:42.300
And those are really
compositional decisions

01:17:42.300 --> 01:17:44.820
which I can make
without making a sound.

01:17:44.820 --> 01:17:49.280
I can think of only
lockers opening

01:17:49.280 --> 01:17:51.960
at the beginning, only
lockers closing at the end.

01:17:51.960 --> 01:17:54.110
That's a compositional decision.

01:17:54.110 --> 01:17:57.030
That came from George Russell.

01:17:57.030 --> 01:18:00.750
You can compose.

01:18:00.750 --> 01:18:03.140
Or, because this is a
class in improvisation,

01:18:03.140 --> 01:18:08.370
you can create sonic ideas
without making a sound.

01:18:08.370 --> 01:18:14.185
And my neurosis as a composer
and as a lifelong student

01:18:14.185 --> 01:18:20.470
of composition, is I want to
use that approach, at least

01:18:20.470 --> 01:18:21.090
to some level.

01:18:21.090 --> 01:18:23.650
Not in everything
